<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Tail" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Tail,</orth> 1) the part of an animal which terminates its body behind: <bibl n="shak. ven 298" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 298</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 298" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 298</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 298" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 298</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ven 298" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 298</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.5.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 5, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 101</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 101</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.329" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 329</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A III, 3, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.154" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.8.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 8, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 10, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.4" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 10, 4</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 3, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 156</bibl>. Metaphorically: <cit><quote>this body hath a t. more perilous than the head,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. IV, 2, 144</bibl></cit>. As for <cit><quote>dragon's t.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.2.140" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 2, 140</bibl></cit>, see <emph>Dragon.</emph><lb />2) backside, arse: <emph>if they</emph> (his eyes) <cit><quote>were set in his t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 2, 13</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>where should I lose my tongue? In thy tale. In thy tail?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 55</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>with my tongue in your t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 219</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) the yard: <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 44</bibl> (quibbling). <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 101</bibl>
<lb />Quibbling between <emph>t.</emph> and <cit><quote>tale:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 3, 55</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 4, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.1.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 1, 8</bibl> <emph>(thereby hangs a t.).</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>